conclusions.Message: [P1] For some query groups, `total_time` > 30% of overall timing, observed on: nodes: `postgres.test1.node`, `postgres.test1.node`, `postgres.test2.node`, `postgres.test2.node`, `postgres.test3.node` and `postgres.test3.node`. Such a high percentage means that those queries are "major contributors" to resource consumption on those nodes. In other words, if a query group has `total_time` which is 30% of overall timing, it means that during the observation period, 30% of time CPUs were working on that node processing queries from this group.
